<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED0BFF89FF54FF20FB01FF50" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B534515BED0BFF89FF54FF20FB01FF50" blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0BFF89FF54FF20FEC0FF18" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED0BFF89FDEAFF21FD5BFF18" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[633,729,150,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denjii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0BFF89FDEAFF21FD5BFF18" box="[633,729,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. denjii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0BFF89FD4DFF20FCB5FF18" bold="true" box="[734,823,150,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED0BFF89FD4DFF20FCB5FF18" box="[734,823,150,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in body pattern and shape of genitalia, but the male can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED0BFF89FE00FF0DFE76FF7C" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[403,500,186,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denjii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0BFF89FE00FF0DFE76FF7C" box="[403,500,186,213]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. denjii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0BFF89FE68FF0CFDD6FF7C" bold="true" box="[507,596,186,212]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED0BFF89FE68FF0CFDD6FF7C" box="[507,596,186,212]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the absence of small denticles on the embolus and the unbranched RTA (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FF0CFF68FEBFFF50" box="[159,317,222,248]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 113–115" captionStart-1="FIGURES 116–118" captionStartId-0="22.[151,264,1961,1985]" captionStartId-1="23.[151,264,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox-0="[152,1428,1165,1936]" captionTargetBox-1="[209,1379,181,1920]" captionTargetId-0="figure-62@22.[151,1437,1153,1937]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@23.[206,1381,181,1935]" captionTargetPageId-0="22" captionTargetPageId-1="23" captionText-0="FIGURES 113–115. Palp of Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., holotype, in ventral (114), prolateral (113) and retrolateral (115) view." captionText-1="FIGURES 116–118. Palp of Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., holotype, in ventral (116), retrolateral (117) and dorsal (118) view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500807" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500811" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6500807/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6500811/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Figs 113–117</figureCitation>
); the female can be distinguished by the different CD path (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FC4BFF68FBF5FF50" box="[984,1143,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 119–123" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-71@24.[151,1436,345,1895]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 119–123. Female genitalia of Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 119, 121. Ventral view; 120, 122. Dorsal view; 123. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500813/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Figs 120, 122</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED0BFF89FF54FEB4FBAEFC60" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" type="description">
<paragraph id="B534515BED0BFF89FF54FEB4FDAAFD2D" blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0BFF89FF54FEB4FE21FEB4" bold="true" box="[199,419,258,284]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FD07FEB4FCB0FEB4" box="[660,818,258,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 107–112" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1033,1057]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-19@22.[151,1436,181,1009]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 107–112. Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (107–108, 110) and female (109, 111–112). 107–109. Habitus, in dorsal (107, 109) and ventral (108) view; 110–111. Front view of carapace; 112. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500805/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Figs 107–108</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 2.01; abdomen length 2.21. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.39, ALE 0.23, PME 0.08, PLE 0.24. Measurements of legs: I 3.18 (1.00, 0.54, 0.74, 0.52, 0.38), II 2.85 (0.93, 0.42, 0.67, 0.50, 0.35), III 3.36 (1.07, 0.51, 0.59, 0.74, 0.45), IV 3.84 (1.11, 0.55, 0.82, 0.89, 0.47). Chelicerae: promargin with two teeth, retromargin with one bicuspid tooth. Palp (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FBE5FED8FA97FE20" box="[1142,1301,366,392]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 113–115" captionStart-1="FIGURES 116–118" captionStartId-0="22.[151,264,1961,1985]" captionStartId-1="23.[151,264,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox-0="[152,1428,1165,1936]" captionTargetBox-1="[209,1379,181,1920]" captionTargetId-0="figure-62@22.[151,1437,1153,1937]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@23.[206,1381,181,1935]" captionTargetPageId-0="22" captionTargetPageId-1="23" captionText-0="FIGURES 113–115. Palp of Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., holotype, in ventral (114), prolateral (113) and retrolateral (115) view." captionText-1="FIGURES 116–118. Palp of Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., holotype, in ventral (116), retrolateral (117) and dorsal (118) view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500807" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500811" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6500807/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6500811/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Figs 113–118</figureCitation>
): bulb bulging; embolus coiled about 1.5 circles, extending towards about seven o’clock direction at origin; embolic disc large and sclerotized, centrally raised, with many grooves; LED relatively thick, serrulate-edged; tegulum not obviously sclerotized, without tegular lobe; salticid radix slightly sclerotized; retrolateral sperm duct loop indistinct in ventral view; retrolateral tibial apophysis thick and wide, intermediately curved. Sternum without setal tuft. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FF76FD94FE07FD94" box="[229,389,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 107–112" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1033,1057]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-19@22.[151,1436,181,1009]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 107–112. Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (107–108, 110) and female (109, 111–112). 107–109. Habitus, in dorsal (107, 109) and ventral (108) view; 110–111. Front view of carapace; 112. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500805/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Figs 107–108</figureCitation>
): carapace dark brown, CPSB frontally white; dorsal abdomen slightly sclerotized, yellowish brown with dark brown markings; ventral abdomen with a large black marking; tibiae I–II, metatarsi I–II and tarsi I–II darker than other leg segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B534515BED0BFF89FF54FD38FE42FC0C" blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0BFF89FF54FD38FEA7FD00" bold="true" box="[199,293,654,680]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FDB6FD38FDFCFD00" box="[549,638,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 107–112" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1033,1057]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-19@22.[151,1436,181,1009]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 107–112. Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (107–108, 110) and female (109, 111–112). 107–109. Habitus, in dorsal (107, 109) and ventral (108) view; 110–111. Front view of carapace; 112. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500805/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig.109</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 2.00; abdomen length 2.60. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.34, ALE 0.25, PME 0.08, PLE 0.23. Measurements of legs: I 2.80 (0.85, 0.43, 0.70, 0.45, 0.37), II 2.87 (0.92, 0.52, 0.59, 0.44, 0.40), III 3.24 (1.05, 0.45, 0.63, 0.65, 0.46), IV 3.66 (1.06, 0.51, 0.78, 0.80, 0.51). Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FF33FD4CFF7CFCBC" box="[160,254,762,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 107–112" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1033,1057]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-19@22.[151,1436,181,1009]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 107–112. Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (107–108, 110) and female (109, 111–112). 107–109. Habitus, in dorsal (107, 109) and ventral (108) view; 110–111. Front view of carapace; 112. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500805/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
) as in male. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FDC5FD4CFD3BFCBC" box="[598,697,762,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 107–112" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1033,1057]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-19@22.[151,1436,181,1009]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 107–112. Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (107–108, 110) and female (109, 111–112). 107–109. Habitus, in dorsal (107, 109) and ventral (108) view; 110–111. Front view of carapace; 112. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500805/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig. 109</figureCitation>
): carapace as in male; abdomen dorsally grayish brown with dark markings, ventrally pale yellow, without large black marking. Sternum without setal tuft. Epigynum (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FB67FCA8FA0DFC90" box="[1268,1423,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 119–123" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-71@24.[151,1436,345,1895]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 119–123. Female genitalia of Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 119, 121. Ventral view; 120, 122. Dorsal view; 123. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500813/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Figs 119, 121</figureCitation>
): window large, rims sclerotized and wide, median septum weakly present; lateral depressions present, relatively deep. Vulva (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0BFF89FEBFFCD0FE4EFC28" box="[300,460,870,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 119–123" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-71@24.[151,1436,345,1895]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 119–123. Female genitalia of Charippus heishiding Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 119, 121. Ventral view; 120, 122. Dorsal view; 123. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500813/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Figs 120, 122</figureCitation>
): CD long and coiled, swerving for 10 times; AG prominent and pointing to axis; spermathecae slightly bulging.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B534515BED0BFF89FF54FC18FBAEFC60" blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1005]" box="[199,1068,942,969]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0BFF89FF54FC18FE07FC60" bold="true" box="[199,389,942,968]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens of the new species were collected on tree trunks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
